{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-press-release-tsx","path":"/media-center/wish-helps-produce-first-ever-arabic-manual-for-doctors-treating-children","result":{"data":{"contentfulPagePressRelease":{"id":"95b4f448-e767-5bde-9381-b56987c57d99","slug":"wish-helps-produce-first-ever-arabic-manual-for-doctors-treating-children","title":"WISH Helps Produce First-Ever Arabic Manual for Doctors Treating Children Injured By Explosives in War Zones ","date":"2019-10-02","filterTags":null,"filterEntity":[{"contentful_id":"5hXcu8ZNa8oEaioiGW486s"}],"heroImage":null,"modulesWrapper":[{"modules":[{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleBodyText","id":"42bc81cd-7b32-5c6f-bf18-bdd003a1136a","text":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>The World Innovation Summit for Health (WISH), an initiative of Qatar Foundation (QF), has published an Arabic version of a manual aimed at providing emergency care for children suffering from blast injuries. </p>\n<p>The Arabic version of the Paediatric Blast Injury Field Manual was launched during the opening of a WISH-curated exhibition at Qatar Museum’s Fire Station on October 1, which is  set to run until October 25. </p>\n<p>The dignitaries in attendance of the opening event included Sheikh Dr. Mohammed Bin Hamad Al-Thani, Director of Public Health, Ministry of Public Health, Qatar; HE Ajay Sharma, the British ambassador to Qatar; HE Franck Gellet, the French ambassador to Qatar; HE Pasquale Salzano, the Italian ambassador to Qatar; HE Stefanie McCollum, the Canadian ambassador to Qatar; and high level representation from the Embassy of Iraq in Qatar. </p>"}}},{"__typename":"ContentfulModuleImageGallery","id":"6f16980c-768e-59b0-aac0-286b6c1385c5","images":[{"caption":null,"image":{"id":"16a88198-0888-5dbd-96c8-3ef006d400c2","title":"Image 1 - WISH Blast injury","file":{"details":{"image":{"width":2038,"height":1116}}},"sizes":{"aspectRatio":1.8666666666666667,"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/2h1qowfuxkq7/ur2LVV6bJkFKbAq42i3J6/446737bcbd5b2